{{update|date=November 2018}}
'''Title 2 of the [[Code of Federal Regulations]]''' (2 CFR), titled '''Grants and Agreements''', is a [[United States]] federal government regulation.

As of the January 1, 2013 revision, Title 2 comprises two subtitles: Subtitle A, [[Office of Management and Budget]] Guidance for Grants and Agreements,<ref>[https://www.costtree.net/sites/default/files/OMB_2-CFR-Part-200_Super_Circular_Desk_Reference_CostTree.pdf 2 CFR Part 200 Super Circular] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160306053300/https://www.costtree.net/sites/default/files/OMB_2-CFR-Part-200_Super_Circular_Desk_Reference_CostTree.pdf |date=2016-03-06 }}</ref> and Subtitle B, Federal Agency Regulations for Grants and Agreements.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.law.cornell.edu/cfr/text/2 | title=2 CFR – Grants and Agreements | date=2013-01-01 | accessdate=2013-03-24 | publisher=[[Cornell University Law School]] Legal Information Institute}}</ref>

