'''A Chronicle of England During the Reigns of the Tudors, From A.D. 1485 to 1559, ''' better known as '''Wriothesley's Chronicle''', was written during the reigns of [[Henry VIII of England|Henry VIII]], [[Edward VI of England|Edward VI]], [[Mary I of England|Mary I]] and [[Elizabeth I of England|Elizabeth I]], by [[Charles Wriothesley]], [[officer of arms]] at the [[College of Arms]] in [[London]]. This [[chronicle]] of [[England|English]] affairs, detailing the accession of [[Henry VII of England|Henry VII]] to the first year of the reign of Elizabeth I, edited by William Douglas Hamilton, was published in two volumes, by the [[Camden Society]] in 1875.{{sfn|Wriothesley I|1875}}{{sfn|Wriothesley II|1875}}

